 travel for several months.\n* Ramirez, Anthony. [https://www.nytimes.com/1993/09/15/business/company-news-more-than-just-a-phone-call-video-conferencing-and-photocopies-too.html More Than Just a Phone Call; Video Conferencing And Photocopies, Too], ''[[The New York Times]]'', September 15, 1993. Discusses the deployment of videoconferencing rooms in several hundred [[Kinkos]] locations.\n* Shannon, Victoria. [https://www.nytimes.com/2007/08/29/technology/29iht-ptend30.1.7299576.html Videoconferencing's virtual leap forward], ''[[The New York Times]]'', August 29, 2007.\n* Sharkey, Joe. [https://www.nytimes.com/2009/05/12/business/12road.html?_r=0 A Meeting in New York? Can't We Videoconference?], ''[[The New York Times]]'', May 11, 2009 online, and in print on May 12, 2009, p. B6 of the New York edition.\n* Vance, Ashlee. [https://www.nytimes.com/2009/10/02/technology/companies/02cisco.html Cisco Buys Norwegian Firm for $3 Billion], ''[[The New York Times]]'', October 1, 2009 online, and October 2, 2009 in print, p. B7. Discusses the acquisition of [[Tandberg]].\n* Wang, Ses [https://web.archive.org/web/20120221043326/http://www.net-security.org/article.php?id=1673 Open source tool detects videoconferencing equipment vulnerabilities], Help Net Security, 17 February 2012.\n* Wayner, Peter. [https://www.nytimes.com/2005/06/16/technology/circuits/16basics.html?pagewanted=all Jerky Pictures and Sound Are History. Videoconferencing Is All Grown Up.], ''[[The New York Times]]'', June 16, 2005.\n\n=== General ===\n\n* Adeshina, Emmanuel. [https://www.nytimes.com/2012/08/07/us/some-criticize-jails-as-they-move-to-video-visits.html?ref=technology&pagewanted=all In-Person Visits Fade as Jails Set Up Video Units for Inmates and Families], ''[[The New York Times]]'' website, August 7, 2012, pg. A15 of the New York Edition.\n* Bajaj, Vikas. [https://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/18/business/global/in-india-an-official-puts-a-webcam-in-office.html Transparent Government, Via Webcams i