ology/circuits/16basics.html?pagewanted=all Jerky Pictures and Sound Are History. Videoconferencing Is All Grown Up.], ''[[The New York Times]]'', June 16, 2005.\n\n=== General ===\n\n* Adeshina, Emmanuel. [https://www.nytimes.com/2012/08/07/us/some-criticize-jails-as-they-move-to-video-visits.html?ref=technology&pagewanted=all In-Person Visits Fade as Jails Set Up Video Units for Inmates and Families], ''[[The New York Times]]'' website, August 7, 2012, pg. A15 of the New York Edition.\n* Bajaj, Vikas. [https://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/18/business/global/in-india-an-official-puts-a-webcam-in-office.html Transparent Government, Via Webcams in India], ''[[The New York Times]]'', July 18, 2011, pg.B3. Published online: July 17, 2011.\n* Davis, Andrew W.; Weinstein, Ira M. [https://web.archive.org/web/20020616194620/http://ess.ntu.ac.uk/miller/videoph.htm The Business Case for Videoconferencing], Wainhouse Research, March 2005.\n* Fairlie, Rik. [http://gadgetwise.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/07/02/skype-puts-video-calls-on-your-tv/ Skype Puts Video Calls on Your TV], ''[[The New York Times]]'', July 2, 2010. \n* Hoffman, Jan. [https://www.nytimes.com/2011/09/25/fashion/therapists-are-seeing-patients-online.html?_r=1 When Your Therapist Is Only a Click Away], ''[[The New York Times]]'', September 25, 2011, pg. ST1. Also published September 23, 2011 online at www.nytimes.com.\n* Miller, Hugh.{{cite web|url=http://ess.ntu.ac.uk/miller/videoph.htm |title=Videophones: The Real Problem |accessdate=2002-06-16 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20020616194620/http://ess.ntu.ac.uk/miller/videoph.htm |archivedate=2002-06-16 }}, Department of Social Sciences, [[Nottingham Trent University]], June 16, 2002. Discusses social issues related to videotelephony.\n* Perlroth, Nicole. [https://www.nytimes.com/2012/01/23/technology/flaws-in-videoconferencing-systems-put-boardrooms-at-risk.html Cameras May Open Up the Board Room to Hackers], ''[[The New York Times|The New York Times online]]'', January 22, 2012. A version of this article appeared in print on January 23, 2012, on page B1 of the New York edition with the headline: \"Conferences Via the Net Called Risky\".\n* ProAV Magazine. [http://www.proavmagazine.com/industry-news.asp?articleID=805312 Being There]{{dead link|date=July 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, ''ProAV Magazine'', November 7, 2008.\n* Saint Louis, Catherine. [https://www.nytimes.com/2012/01/11/us/music-lessons-on-webcams-grow-in-popularity.html With Enough Bandwidth, Many Join The Band], ''[[The New York Times]]'', January 10, 2012 (online), January 11, 2012 (in print, New York Edition, pg. A1). Retrieved online January 11, 2012. Synopsis: a look at the pros and cons of videotelephony used for private, individual, music lessons.\n* Steinberg, Neil. [https://www.forbes.com/2007/10/13/neil-steinberg-videophone-tech-future07-cx_ns_1015gizmo.html Dude, Where's My Video Phone?], ''[[Forbes#Forbes.com|Forbes.com]]'' website, October 15, 2007\n\n=== Environmental benefits{{dubious|Environmental benefits?|date=April 2017}} ===\n\n* Biello, David. [http://www.scientificamerican.com/article.cfm?id=can-videoconferencing-replace-travel Can Videoconferencing Replace Travel?], ''[[Scientific American]]'', March 18, 2009.\n* Coroama, V.C., et al. [http://www.worldresourcesforum.org/files/Article%20Coroama%20Hilty%20Birtel.pdf Effects of Internet-Based Multiple-Site Conferences on Greenhouse Gas Emissions], ''Telematics and Informatics'', 2011, doi:10.1016/j.tele.2011.11.006\n* Pachner, Joanna. [https://www.theglobeandmail.com/report-on-business/small-business/sb-digital/innovation/the-next-best-thing-to-being-there/article1207106/ The Next Best Thing to Being There], Toronto: ''[[The Globe and Mail]]'', October 13, 2009.\n\n=== Historical and technical ===\n\n* Ebel, H. \"Subjective Assessment of Picture Interference in the Videophone\" in [https://books.google.com/books?id=IiURF1cH0YUC 4th International Symposium on Human Factors in Telephony], Bad Wiessee, Germany, September 23\u201327, 1968, Information Gatekeepers Inc., pp.&nbsp;289\u2013298.\n* Fischer, K.; Ebel, H.; \"Problems Of How To Position Users In Front Of The Videophone\" in: [https://books.google.com/books?id=IiURF1cH0YUC 4th International Symposium on Human Factors in Telephony], Bad Wiessee, Germany, September 23\u201327, 1968, Information Gatekeepers Inc., pp.&nbsp;269\u2013282.\n* Hall, A.D. \"Experiments with Picturephone Service\" in: ''Bell Laboratories RECORD'', 1964, Vol. 42, pp.&nbsp;114\u2013120.\n* [[Herbert E. Ives|Ives, Herbert E.]] [https://books.google.com/books?id=WqkmPh-QtQYC Two-Way Television and a Pictorial Account of its Background] in: ''Bell Laboratories Record'', 1930, Vol. 8, pp.&nbsp;399\u2013404, and [http://www.tvhistory.tv/1930-ATT-BELL.htm viewable online here].\n* <!-- <ref name=\"Bell Telephone Quarterly Vol XI-1932.04.p.78\"> -->[[Herbert E. Ives|Ives, Herbert E.]]. [https://archive.org/details/belltelephonemag11amerrich Picture Transmission and Television] in: ''Bell Labs Quarterly'', April 1932, Vol. 11, pp.&nbsp;118\u2013142.\n* Jaur, Francis. \"Usage Domestiques du Visiophone\", Technologies de l'Information et Soci\u00e9t\u00e9, 2, 1990, pp.&nbsp;89\u2013102. (French)\n* Schunack, Von Johannes; Maly, Rolf. [http://www.cdvandt.org/Band1Heft4Juli%2739.pdf#page=28 Die Fernseh-Sprechtechnik] in: ''Fernseh A.G.: 10 Jahre'', Berlin: Hausmitteilungen Aus Forshunsg Und Betrieb Der Fernseh Aktiengellschaft, July 1939, pp.&nbsp;138\u2013143. (PDF, German)\n* Schulte, Olaf A. [http://www.seer.nomos.de/fileadmin/muk/doc/MuK_02_04.pdf#page=77 \"The Next Best Thing To Being There\"\u2014Ein \u00dcberblick Zu 25 Jahren Videokonferenzforschung] (An Overview of 25 years of videoconferencing research) in: ''Medien & Kommunikations-wissenschaft'', Baden-Baden: [[Hans-Bredow-Institut]], April 2002, pp.&nbsp;551\u2013570 (PDF, German).\n\n== External links ==\n\n{{Wiktionary|videophone}}\n{{Commons category|Videotelephony}}\n{{Commons|Videotelephony#Videoconferencing_systems_and_components|Videoconferencing systems and components}}\n\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20130517040414/http://techchannel.att.com/play-video.cfm/2012/6/29/AT%26T-Archives-Debut-of-the-Picturephone Debut of the First Picturephone], 1970 video courtesy of AT&T Archives and History Center, Warren, N.J.\n* [http://www.britishpathe.com/video/videophone/query/telephones British Path\u00e9 news clip: Videophone 1970], a movie reel news clip on the assembly and demonstration of a prototype British General Post Office 'Viewphone' at Taplow, Buckinghamshire; (February 1, 1970; video, 1:16 seconds length)\n* [http://forums.whirlpool.net.au/archive/181174 Wirlpool Forums: Movies that feature videophones]\n\n{{Telephony}}\n{{Telecommunications}}\n{{Computer-mediated communication}}\n\n[[Category:Assistive technology]]\n[[Category:Computing input devices]]\n[[Category:Film and video technology]]\n[[Category:Groupware]]\n[[Category:Health informatics]]\n[[Category:Smartphones]]\n[[Category:Science fiction themes]]\n[[Category:Technology in society]]\n[[Category:Telecommunication services]]\n[[Category:Teleconferencing]]\n[[Category:Video]]\n[[Category:Videotelephony]]\n[[Category:Articles containing video clips]]\n", "name_user": "Dissident93", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eDescriptive names and terminology", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Videotelephony"}
{"title_page": "Hermann Behrbohm", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name = Hermann Behrbohm\n| image = Hermann Behrbohm N\u00e4rbild SAAB.jpg\n| caption = <small>Hermann Behrbohm. Foto cirka 1955.</small>\n| birth_date = 30 October 1907\n| birth_place = {{flag|German Empire}} [[Karlsruhe]] [[Grand Duchy of Baden]]\n| death_date = {{death date and age | 1977 | 10 | 12 | 1907 | 10 | 30}}\n| death_place = {{Flag|United Kingdom}} Fingelsham [[Northbourne]] [[Kent (county) | Kent]] [[England]]\n| spouse = 1940-1964 Lilli Walter (divorced), 5 children <br /> 1964-1977 Pamela Leach (his death), 1 child\n| children =\n| nationality =\n| citizenship =\n| known_for = Expert in [[Aerodynamics]] and [[Strength of materials|Strength]] in fighter aircraft <br /> [[Messerschmitt Bf 109]] <br /> [[Saab 32 Lansen]] <br /> [[Saab 35 Draken]] <br /> [[Saab 105]] <br /> [[Saab 37 Viggen]]\n| awards = Swedish Aeronautical Society's Thulin Medal <small> (1968) </small>\n| website =\n| education = [[Georg-August-Universit\u00e4t G\u00f6ttingen]] [[Mathematics]] (Ph.D., 1944)\n| employer =\n| occupation = Aircraft design / construction\n| title = Ph.D\n}}\n[[File:AIRPOWER16 - Air to Air SK35C Draken (color).jpg|thumb|[[Saab 35 Draken]]]]\n[[File:Saab JA37 37447 Swedish Air Force Marcel van Leeuwen.jpg| thumb|[[Saab 37 Viggen]]]]\n'''Otto ''Hermann'' Bernhard Behrbohm''', born [[October 30]] [[1907]] in [[Karlsruhe]], [[Grand Duchy of Baden]], [[Imperial Germany]], dead [[October 12]] [[1977]] Fingelsham, [[Northbourne]], [[Kent (county) | Kent]], [[United Kingdom]], was a German [[mathematician]] active in Sweden and Germany.\n\n== Biography==\nHermann Behrbohm was significant in the design of [[Saab 35 Draken]] and [[Saab 37 Viggen]]. He received the Swedish Aeronautical Society\u2019s Thulin Medal [[1968]] in silver for having promoted aviation technology with work.<ref>\"[https://ftfsweden.se/thulinmedaljen/ Flygtekniska F\u00f6reningen Thulinmedaljen]\"</ref><ref>\"[https://ftfsweden.se/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Silvermedalj\u00f6rer-1944-2015.pdf Flygtekniska F\u00f6reningen Thulinmedaljen Silvermedalj\u00f6rer-1944-2015]\"</ref>\n\nHe made efforts in aviation technology in several countries during his life, due to the circumstances. Finally, as a [[pensioner]], [[1972]] he moved to [[England]] with his British wife. His children stayed in Sweden.\n\nHe authored many articles in aerodynamic and mathematical specialist press available on libraries and the Internet.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hermann Behrbohm|url=https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/Hermann-Behrbohm/103029554|publisher=Semantic Scholar|accessdate=2020-02-06}}</ref>\n\n=== Education and doctoral dissertation in Germany ===\nHe studied mechanical engineering at the Technical University of Karlsruhe, as well as [[mathematics]] and [[number theory]] at [[Georg-August-Universit\u00e4t G\u00f6ttingen]].\n\nBehrbohm was a research assistant at the Georg-August-Universit\u00e4t G\u00f6ttingen in 1933\u20131936 and wrote his doctoral dissertation on the [[algebra]] identity of the meromorphisms of an [[elliptical function]] body. The thesis was not approved for political reasons when the supervisor was [[Jewish]] and [[Nazi Germany]] took over.<ref>[https://www.abebooks.com/book-search/author/behrbohm-hermann/ \u00dcber die Algebraizit\u00e4t der Meromorphismen eines elliptischen Funktionenk\u00f6rpers Nachrichten von der Gesellschaft der Wissenschaften zu G\u00f6ttingen, Reihe:Mathematisch-Physikalische Klasse - Fachgruppe 1 Mathematik Neue Folge Band 1 - Nr.8, Behrbohm Hermann: Published by Berlin, Weidmann Verlag, 1935]</ref> In 1944 he was promoted [[doctor]] in [[mathematics]] and [[physics]].\n\nBehrbohm also had great difficulties in marrying his first wife because of the regulations in Nazi Germany. She had difficulties obtaining biological purity certificates (unknown father) and thus being able to marry him, which was possible only in 1940.\n\n=== Messerschmitt===\nHe was recruited in 1937 to [[Messerschmitt]]\u2019s [[Aerodynamics]] department in [[Augsburg]]. He was also involved in a part-time  assignment from 1944 at the Ministry of Aviation in [[Vienna]].\n\n=== French occupation ===\nAs a Messerschmitt employee, he [[1945]] was initially a [[prisoner of war]] but [[1946]] was recruited by BEE (French Aerodynamic Research and Development Institute) with operations in [[Emmendingen]] and [[Weil am Rhein]] in [[French occupation zone in Germany]].\n\nAfter the formation of the [[Federal Republic of Germany]] [[1949]] and the cessation of occupation, the opportunities were greater to find scientifically interesting work abroad and Behrbohm received offers from France and other countries.\n\n=== Saab===\nHermann chose [[1951]] to start working on [[Saab AB | Saab]] moving to [[Link\u00f6ping]] with his family who became naturalized Swedes.\nThe motives for choosing to work for Saab were the projects [[Saab 32 Lansen]] and [[Saab 35 Draken]] under [[Erik Bratt]] and [[Tore Gullstrand]].<ref> \"[https://www.e-pic.se/Aircraft/Aircraft-sorted-by-type/SAAB/SAAB-32-Lansen/i-bpQqNfS Note that Herman Behbohm was a French prisoner of war in 1945 and came not (as claimed) with [[Frid W\u00e4nstr\u00f6m]] and the Messerschmitt drawings that Saab acquired in Switzerland in 1945 that laid the foundation for [[Saab 29 Tunnan]], ref Margareta Behrbohm] \"</ref> Being a specialist in aerodynamics is a narrow labor market with few employers in the world who have sufficient resources to create good results. Saab where they built up operations and Sweden's ambitions gave Hermann the opportunities.\n\nHermann remained at Saab until his retirement in 1972. During the years 1960-64 he was head of the [[Aerodynamics]] department, also participated in the projects [[Saab 37 Viggen]] and [[Saab 105]] and published a large number of articles in aerodynamics.<ref>\"[http://runeberg.org/tektid/1952/1078.html Teknisk Tidskrift / \u00c5rg\u00e5ng 82. 1952 / 1062]\"</ref> He was esteemed and won the Swedish Aeronautical Society\u2019s Thulin Medal [[1968]] in silver.\n\nHermann Behrbohm and [[Bertil Dillner]] made significant efforts in the design of [[Saab 37 Viggen]], and in particular the design and tests of the nose wing construction.<ref>\"[http://libris.kb.se/bib/11717818 Flyghistorisk revy, 0345-3413, System 37 Viggen, Artikel av Erik Bratt]\"</ref>\n\nAfter retirement, he moved with his second wife to her home town in the south [[England]] and lived there afterwards.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of aviators]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Behrbohm, Hermann}}\n[[Category: Men]]\n[[Category: People from Karlsruhe]]\n[[Category:1907 births]]\n[[Category:1977 deaths]]\n[[Category:Aircraft designers]]\n[[Category:20th-century men]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name = Hermann Behrbohm\n| image = Hermann Behrbohm N\u00e4rbild SAAB.jpg\n| caption = <small>Hermann Behrbohm. Foto cirka 1955.</small>\n| birth_date = 30 October 1907\n| birth_place = {{flag|German Empire}} [[Karlsruhe]] [[Grand Duchy of Baden]]\n| death_date = {{death date and age | 1977 | 10 | 12 | 1907 | 10 | 30}}\n| death_place = {{Flag|United Kingdom}} Fingelsham [[Northbourne]] [[Kent (county) | Kent]] [[England]]\n| spouse = 1940-1964 Lilli Walter (divorced), 5 children <br /> 1964-1977 Pamela Leach (his death), 1 child\n| children =\n| nationality =\n| citizenship =\n| known_for = Expert in [[Aerodynamics]] and [[Strength of materials|Strength]] in fighter aircraft <br /> [[Messerschmitt Bf 109]] <br /> [[Saab 32 Lansen]] <br /> [[Saab 35 Draken]] <br /> [[Saab 105]] <br /> [[Saab 37 Viggen]]\n| awards = Swedish Aeronautical Society's Thulin Medal <small> (1968) </small>\n| website =\n| education = [[Georg-August-Universit\u00e4t G\u00f6ttingen]] [[Mathematics]] (Ph.D., 1944)\n| employer =\n| occupation = Aircraft design / construction\n| title = Ph.D\n}}\n[[File:AIRPOWER16 - Air to Air SK35C Draken (color).jpg|thumb|[[Saab 35 Draken]]]]\n[